<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MOLESTER OF 3 DEAF CAMPERS SENTENCED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Aformer camp counselor was sentenced Thursday to a year in County Jail for 
molesting three teen-agers at a Castaic camp for deaf children this summer. 
</P>
<P>
In a plea bargain with prosecutors, Martin Luther Willis, 19, pleaded no 
contest in August to charges of sodomy, sexual battery and child molestation. 
</P>
<P>
The incidents involved two 16-year-olds and a 13-year-old. 
</P>
<P>
Willis, who is deaf, was arrested Aug. 10 at the Lion's of California/Nevada 
Wilderness Camp for Deaf Children. 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles County sheriff's deputies were called to the camp after a camp 
official learned about the molestations from a teen-ager there. 
</P>
<P>
Willis had been a counselor at the camp for two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
Had the case gone to trial, Willis could have faced nine years in state prison. 
</P>
<P>
Prosecutors agreed to the plea bargain because of Willis' age and to prevent 
the victims from having to testify. 
</P>
</TEXT>
