<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: CANOGA PARK WOMAN DIES IN HEAD-ON CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One woman was killed and three motorists injured when two cars collided in a 
Reseda intersection, Los Angeles police said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Florida Rivera, 50, of Canoga Park was killed about 6:30 p.m. Wednesday when 
the car in which she was a passenger was struck head-on by a car on Saticoy 
Street at Tampa Avenue, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Dagoberto Barrera, 31, of Canoga Park was driving west on Saticoy Street with 
Rivera when an eastbound car driven by Patricia Aguado, 19, of North Hollywood 
turned in front of them, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Barrera, Aguado and Aguado's passenger, Latanya Davis, 26, of North Hollywood 
suffered minor injuries in the collision. 
</P>
<P>
Police said Aguado was not cited, but an investigation was continuing. 
</P>
