<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTY IN BRIEF: TARZANA; 
</P>
<P>
HOSPITAL FINED FOR TOXIC GAS EXPOSURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
State job-safety inspectors have fined a Tarzana hospital nearly $5,000 after a 
technician was exposed to a suspected cancer-causing gas leaking from a machine 
used to sterilize surgical instruments. But Cal/OSHA officials dropped more 
than $12,000 in additional fines against Tarzana Regional Medical Center after 
deciding that they could not prove the hospital didn't have proper mechanical 
controls to prevent future leaks, a spokesman said. The hospital was cited on 
Oct. 2 for 18 violations of state worker-protection laws, including five repeat 
offenses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
