<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: DORSEY HIGH WINS COUNTY MOCK TRIAL 
CHAMPIONSHIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dorsey High School in Baldwin Hills has won the Los Angeles County Mock Trial 
championships, snatching the crown from Louisville High School in Woodland 
Hills. 
</P>
<P>
Students presented trial arguments in a drunk driving felony manslaughter case. 
The young "lawyers" had to argue the constitutionality of the arrest and of 
sobriety checkpoints. 
</P>
<P>
Dorsey will now advance to the state competition, set for April in Sacramento. 
The mock trial is sponsored by the Constitutional Rights Foundation, a 
nonprofit organization that educates the public on legal issues. 
</P>
<P>
More than 40 high schools took part in this year's competition, which was held 
at Los Angeles Superior Courthouse, with Judge Judith Chirlin presiding and a 
panel of three attorneys scoring the teams. 
</P>
</TEXT>
