<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: POLLSTER CLOSING FIRM TO JOIN D.A.'S OFFICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Stephen Teichner, a prominent California pollster, will join the Los Angeles 
County district attorney's office as a "special assistant for criminal justice 
planning," Dist. Atty. 
</P>
<P>
Ira Reiner said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Teichner, 47, said he will do no polling in his new position. 
</P>
<P>
In a written statement, Reiner said Teichner will work as a consultant on 
community-relations issues such as consumer protection, victim assistance and 
hate crimes. 
</P>
<P>
Teichner Associates, founded in 1976, will close Jan. 7. The Orange 
County-based firm had developed a national reputation and was relied on 
extensively by the news media and political candidates for its weekly polls 
during state and national elections. 
</P>
<P>
Teichner's salary will be $69,150, said Sandi Gibbons, a spokeswoman for the 
district attorney's office. 
</P>
</TEXT>
