<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: CORONER'S PROBE FINDS GIRL WAS STRANGLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A teen-age girl found dead in her East Los Angeles home last week was 
strangled, the coroner's office said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Mirabel Perez, 14, was found slain in the bedroom of her home on South Gage 
Avenue last Friday by a classmate who was picking her up for school, sheriff's 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
It was not immediately known how Perez died, but an autopsy showed she was 
strangled with an unknown object, coroner's spokesman Bob Dambacher said. 
</P>
<P>
Sheriff's investigators were not available to comment Thursday and a department 
spokesman had no information about any arrests or a motive for the slaying. 
</P>
