101 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Scorsese Honored: Director Martin Scorsese will be the sixth recipient of the 
American Cinematheque Award at the Cinematheque's annual "Moving Picture Ball" 
on March 22 in Los Angeles -- three days before the Academy Awards. Reached on 
location in Florida where he is shooting "Cape Fear," Scorsese said he is 
pleased at the honor, "especially since it is for the benefit of the 
Cinematheque," a cause he has long supported. Cinematheque chairman Sydney 
Pollack said the organization seeks to build a film complex in Hollywood near 
Mann's Chinese Theater as part of a redevelopment program. CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Scorsese 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
