<TEXT>
<P>
BLEAK PROFILE: The county's Homeless Issues Task Force gives this rough 
description of our homeless population: Most are between 25 and 49, the largest 
segment in their 30s. Two-thirds are male, and nearly two-thirds are white. . . 
. More than a quarter have children, and 18% have more than one. 
</P>
<P>
Half the children are 5 years or younger. Eleven percent are working; 67% are 
looking for work. . . . Almost half have been homeless for more than a year, 
almost a quarter for more than three years. Four in 10 have been county 
residents for more than 10 years. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
THE EDUCATED HOMELESS 
</P>
<P>
Though below the country norm, many homeless have graduated from high school 
and many went to college. 
</P>
<P>
