<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; 
</P>
<P>
COLLEGE BOARD ELECTS BIOLOGIST PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Marcia Milchiker has been elected president of the Saddleback Community College 
District Board of Trustees, replacing Joan J. Hueter. 
</P>
<P>
Milchiker, a Laguna Hills research biologist, was elected this week during a 
secret ballot at the board's annual organizational meeting. 
</P>
<P>
She was vice president during the past year. 
</P>
<P>
It is the first time that Milchiker, who has been a trustee since 1985, has 
been president of the eight-member board. The president conducts the board's 
meetings, appoints committees and represents the board at various on- and 
off-campus functions. 
</P>
<P>
Milchiker said a focus of her term will be the search for a third campus site 
in the district, in addition to Saddleback and Irvine Valley colleges. 
</P>
<P>
Trustee Robert L. Moore was elected vice president, and Hueter was elected 
clerk. 
</P>
</TEXT>
