<HEADLINE>
<P>
WALTER BOWMAN IS NEW CYPRESS MAYOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CYPRESS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Walter Bowman was chosen as mayor this week, beating out fellow council member 
Gail H. Kerry for the position. 
</P>
<P>
Bowman, a real-estate agent, was nominated by former Mayor Cecilia L. Age. 
</P>
<P>
Casting votes in his favor were Age and newly elected Councilman Richard 
Partin. Bowman received three votes, including his own. 
</P>
<P>
"I plan on representing all of the interests in the community," said Bowman, 
who narrowly regained his council seat in November. 
</P>
<P>
Kerry, who was nominated for the position by newcomer Joyce C. Nicholson, was 
backed by members of Concerned Citizens of Cypress. Nicholson is the president 
of the citizens' group. 
</P>
<P>
Kerry was elected to the council in 1985 and was instrumental in defeating a 
proposal to build a large industrial park in one of the last open spaces in the 
city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
