<HEADLINE>
<P>
CORONA DEL MAR'S CARLSEN ALL-AMERICAN IN VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lara Carlsen of Corona del Mar High School, The Times' Orange County girls' 
volleyball player of the year, has been named to Volleyball Monthly magazine's 
All-American first team, the magazine announced Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Carlsen, a 5-foot-11 senior middle blocker, averaged 14 kills a match and led 
the Sea Kings to the State Division I and Southern Section 5-A championships. 
She has made an oral commitment to play at USC next season. 
</P>
<P>
La Habra's Missy Clements, a 5-11 senior middle blocker, was named to the 
magazine's All-American second team. Clements, who is undecided on a college, 
led the Highlanders to their second consecutive State Division II and Southern 
Section 3-A titles this season. 
</P>
<P>
Carlsen and Clements also were among several Orange County players named to the 
all-Southern Section teams, which were released Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
County players on the all-Southern Section teams: 
</P>
<P>
Division 5-A 
</P>
<P>
First team: MVPs -- Carlsen (Corona del Mar) and Tracy Schriber (Corona del 
Mar). Others -- Marta Bickert (El Toro), Kealy Clarke (Laguna Beach), Tara 
Kroesch (Newport Harbor), Michelle Mauney (El Toro), Tanya Mitchell (Capistrano 
Valley), Prentice Perkins (Corona del Mar). 
</P>
<P>
Second team: Brandi Brooks (Estancia), Christine Garner (Tustin), Bryn Gillis 
(Dana Hills), Judy Jackson (Capistrano Valley), Megan Morse (Santa Margarita), 
Stacy Petersen (Corona del Mar), Ashley Wacholder (Laguna Beach). 
</P>
<P>
Division 4-A 
</P>
<P>
First team: Cristin Rossman (Marina). 
</P>
<P>
Second team: Stacey Blackburn (Marina), Julie Greer (Esperanza), Debbie Howard 
(Edison), Heather Lowe (Cypress), Shelby Snyder (Fountain Valley). 
</P>
<P>
Division 3-A 
</P>
<P>
First team: MVP -- Clements (La Habra). Others -- Melizza Benitez (El Modena), 
Marni Hichborn (El Modena), Ana Kristich (La Habra), Zrinka Kristich (La 
Habra). 
</P>
<P>
Second team: Lisa Almanza (La Habra), Kathy Farina (El Modena), Kori Rosenkranz 
(Sunny Hills). 
</P>
<P>
Division 1-A 
</P>
<P>
First team: Kathleen Bunce (Capistrano Valley Christian), Karen Benkovsky 
(Capistrano Valley Christian). 
</P>
<P>
Second team: Elaine Kollias (Capistrano Valley Christian), Jennifer Rudometkin 
(Whittier Christian). 
</P>
<P>
Small Schools Division 
</P>
<P>
First team: Susan Teitsworth (St. Margaret's). 
</P>
<P>
Second team: Hilary Albers (St. Margaret's). 
</P>
