<HEADLINE>
<P>
MILLER HITS NINE THREE-POINTERS, EDISON GIRLS FINISH IN FIFTH PLACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Erika Miller made nine three-point baskets and scored 43 points to lead Edison 
High School to a 73-32 victory over Los Amigos Thursday in a fifth-place game 
of the Savanna girls' basketball tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Miller's nine three-pointers were one short of the Southern Section record, 
accomplished twice last season by former teammate Debbie Fischer. 
</P>
<P>
Angie Cole of Royal also made 10 in a game last season. 
</P>
<P>
"I was looking to shoot (three-pointers) because there was nobody guarding me 
-- they played a zone," Miller said. "So the coach told me to keep shooting." 
</P>
<P>
Teammate Joan Paje added two three-pointers to help set a school team record of 
11 in a game. 
</P>
<P>
Miller, a 5-6 senior, is averaging 24.2 points and has connected on 22 of 51 
three-point attempts this season. Edison is 9-2. 
</P>
<P>
In other Savanna tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
Loara 42, Newport Harbor 31 -- Tracy Titus scored 19 points and Stephanie 
Wright added 12 points to lead Loara (4-3). 
</P>
<P>
Savanna 58, Torrey Pines 36 -- Carrie Frederick had 22 points, Stacey Aliff 18 
and Sara Works added 14 to lead Savanna (7-0) in a championship semifinal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
