<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
PAGETT SETS LONG-RANGE RECORD IN RANCHO SANTIAGO'S VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Brett Pagett set a single-game record for Rancho Santiago College with seven 
three-pointers in a 99-75 victory over Moorpark in the semifinals of the 
Pasadena Tournament Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Pagett was seven of nine from three-point range and nine of 11 overall. 
</P>
<P>
He surpassed the record of six, which was set by Kenny Ammann (1988) and Gene 
Altamirano, who did it twice last season. Pagett also had six assists. 
</P>
<P>
Erik Martin scored 18 points and had 10 rebounds for Rancho Santiago (12-1), 
the top-ranked team in the state. 
</P>
<P>
In the Riverside men's tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton 104, Mt. San Jacinto 53 -- Bob Terry had 29 points and Garry Hunter 
16 for Fullerton (8-5), which plays Golden West at 4 p.m. today in a 
consolation semifinal. 
</P>
<P>
Golden West 110, Chaffey 107 -- Ric Van Scoyoc scored 27 points, Scott Campbell 
26 -- including five three-pointers -- and Jason Vaughan 24 for Golden West 
(5-8). 
</P>
<P>
In the Cuesta women's tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Orange Coast 73, Hartnell 53 -- Kami Bigler scored 17 for Orange Coast in the 
first-round game. 
</P>
<P>
In a nonconference women's game: 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback 92, Palomar 27 -- Nilda Valdez scored 19 points, Kristen Okura added 
18 points, and Erin Schimeneck had 16 points, 12 rebounds and five blocked 
shots for host Saddleback (8-2). 
</P>
