<P>
BLAST, FIRE RAZE FAIRFAX BUILDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An explosion and fire destroyed a Fairfax district commercial building early 
today, the fire department said. 
</P>
<P>
City Fire Battalion Chief Carlton Callaway said the force of the 1:47 a.m. 
explosion knocked a man to the ground standing 150 feet away and sent shards of 
glass flying across the street. No injuries were reported. 
</P>
<P>
Arson is suspected and investigators found traces of flammable liquids in the 
building, Callaway said. 
</P>
<P>
Six stores located within the building were damaged and an appliance store and 
a neighboring carpet store were a total loss, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Traffic near the busy intersection of Pico Boulevard and Fairfax Avenue was 
diverted at least four hours. 
</P>
